# MyUS Project Constitution

## Technology Stack

- Frontend: React
- Backend: Spring Boot
- Database: SQL Server
- Authentication: JWT

## Architecture Principles

- Follow Clean Architecture principles.
- Separate Presentation, Business Logic, and Data Access layers.
- Use RESTful APIs for communication.

## Code Quality

- Use meaningful naming conventions.
- Follow coding standards and best practices.
- All new features must be documented.

## Security

- All users must be authenticated before accessing protected resources.
- Role-based authorization for Student and Administrator.
- Sensitive data must not be exposed in APIs.

## Database

- Use normalized database design.
- Maintain referential integrity through foreign keys.

## Testing

- Critical business logic should be tested.
- API endpoints should be validated before deployment.

## Documentation

- Major features must include user stories and acceptance criteria.
- System design decisions should be documented.

## Governance

This constitution is the authoritative guide for project planning, architecture, quality, and release readiness.
Amendments require updating this document, reviewing changes with collaborators, and bumping the constitution version.

Versioning policy:
- MAJOR version when governance, principles, or section structure changes materially.
- MINOR version when new mandatory sections are added.
- PATCH version for clarifications, wording updates, or non-substantive edits.

Compliance review:
- Every pull request must reference this constitution and explain how proposed work complies with one or more sections.
- Reviewers should flag changes that introduce hidden scope, weaken architecture boundaries, or bypass documented quality/security requirements.
- Automated hooks are optional helpers, not substitutes for explicit agreement.

